snippet.textDisplay:
A friend of mine has a CDL and drives the International variant for work. She wants a pickup version after driving that truck, and she's otherwise against everything smaller than that and larger than her compact sedan.


Personally, I prefer the older ones where the body lines actually match the cab better. I also find my '87 F-150 to be obscenely large, so I'd never actually own one of these behemoths. I am, however, glad that other people do. It's fun to see them on the road.
